Maven:
*)It is a build testing tool / build management tool which is used for build creation & build testing 
& build deployment. 
*)Developers use this tool for build creation, build installation and build deployment.
*)In Automation we use it for build testing and also to handle dependencies.

Advantages:
1)Handling dependent jars
2)It provide a quick setup for new Automations Engineer
3)We can execute Automations Script from cmd prompt
4)Maven support Jenkins tool

 Maven Commands:
1)mvn clean : used to clean the reports present in target folder
2)mvn validate : used to validate the entire framework
3)mvn compile : use to check the compilation and integration issue and if any jar is missing it will start downloading the jar automatically
4)mvn test : used to execute all the test scripts in src/test/java


mvn -e for error stack trace as well


If plugin is not added and you run mvn test all with _test prefix will run if surefire plugin is added all mentioned in suitexml tag will be executed

We need to download maven apache download zip file to run our testcases via command prompt
once downloaded and extracted paste path of downloaded folder in  uservariable m2_home
path - add in path variable path till bin folder
open project and select project do right click show in system explorer
in naviagation bar open cmd
type mvn -version - should display the added version

mvn -Dtest=ClassName test -- to run individual script via command prompt
mvn test if we want to run all 6 test cases
mvn test -P ID    -- This is command to run profile base xml and id will specify which ID

If you have multiple xml suites you can run them by adding profiles of each
If we give ID A only A will execute if we give B only B having xml suite only that will execute

*)Surefire-plugin:-
<build>
	<plugins>
		<plugin>
			<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
			<artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
			<version>3.2.5</version>
			<configuration>
				<suiteXmlFiles>
					<suiteXmlFile>batch.xml</suiteXmlFile>
					<suiteXmlFile>ST.xml</suiteXmlFile>
				</suiteXmlFiles>
			</configuration>
		</plugin>
	</plugins>
</build>

*)profiling:-
<profiles>
		<profile>
			<id>A</id>
			<build>
				<plugins>
					<plugin>
						<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
						<artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
						<version>3.2.3</version>
						<configuration>
							<suiteXmlFiles>
								<suiteXmlFile>ft.xml</suiteXmlFile>
							</suiteXmlFiles>
						</configuration>
					</plugin>
				</plugins>
			</build>
		</profile>
		<profile>
			<id>B</id>
			<build>
				<plugins>
					<plugin>
						<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
						<artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
						<version>3.2.3</version>
						<configuration>
							<suiteXmlFiles>
								<suiteXmlFile>IT.xml</suiteXmlFile>
							</suiteXmlFiles>
						</configuration>
					</plugin>
				</plugins>
			</build>
		</profile>
		<profile>
			<id>C</id>
			<build>
				<plugins>
					<plugin>
						<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
						<artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
						<version>3.2.3</version>
						<configuration>
							<suiteXmlFiles>
								<suiteXmlFile>ST.xml</suiteXmlFile>
							</suiteXmlFiles>
						</configuration>
					</plugin>
				</plugins>
			</build>
		</profile>
	</profiles>
	
	maven command:-
D- define
P-profile

1)to execute one script from command prompt:- mvn test -Dtest=Script1_Test
2)to execute entire script:- mvn test
3)to execute xml suite:- add the surefire plugin in pom.xml & mvn test in command prompt
4)profiling:- mvn test -P id 


